rComments: Professor Brauen is an outstanding professor. Every lecture was engaging and even when the material was hard, Professor Brauen put a lot of effort into clarifying concepts exceptionally clearly. Professor Brauen is extremely fair and caring towards his students. I would highly recommend his courses, any student would be very lucky to have him.

Glenn is a very smart guy, he knows everything about GIS and that being said, his teaching at the introductory level is at a level too advanced for actually introducing a topic. The assignments are weighted very low and he will help you so you can do well. The exams are tricky though.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: This class is very easy to get good grades as tutorials and assignments have step by step guides. His lectures can be a little bit boring at times but can also be very interesting. There are also lecture exercises. He is very approachable and will explain concepts to you until you understand it. Would definitely take more of his other classes.

Glenn is a decent professor and the lecture material isn't too hard to handle.  To get a good mark, you NEED to make sure you understand everything he teaches and makes you do in the assignments.  Everything in lectures and assignments will show up on exams.  This is one of those courses where things can be confusing but it's up to you to get help.

Lecture: reading off of slides in monotone voice. Learned more from readings & on own than lectures but attendance mandatory. Course difficulty is only b/c assignments very unclear & prof does not successfully clarify instructions when asked, & shuts down further inquiries. Prof attitude is poor. Worst course experience by far out of 20 I've taken.
